  <div class="tone-junior"><p>Fill out both forms incompletely and hit submit. The "Summary" mode shows all errors at the top in a red box. The "Inline" mode shows errors directly below the offending field. Notice how much easier it is to find and fix errors in the inline version.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-mid"><p>The demo measures time-to-successful-resubmit from the first failed submit attempt. Inline errors are typically 55–70% faster on recovery, since users don't need to context-switch between the error list and the fields.</p></div>
  <div class="tone-staff"><p>Pay attention to the error copy in both modes. The summary mode uses short labels ("Invalid email"). The inline mode uses actionable copy with examples. Even if both were inline, the actionable copy would be faster, since discoverability and actionability are separate dimensions.</p></div>

